      "resolution_level": 5,
      "anchor_concept_id": "spine_biology_l3_autoimmunity",
      "content": {
        "title": "Rheumatoid Arthritis Pathogenesis",
        "definition": "Chronic symmetric polyarthritis driven by autoantibodies (RF, anti-CCP), T-cell activation, and cytokine-mediated synovial inflammation with pannus formation.",
        "summary": "Anti-CCP antibodies are highly specific for RA. TNF and IL-6 drive synovitis and joint destruction."
